        "section_value": "Chief Complaint\nNeck pain following a motor vehicle collision.\nHistory of Present Illness\nThe patient reports neck pain following a car accident approximately one week prior. He describes the injury as a forward head movement with rapid acceleration, resulting in pain. The patient rates the pain as 7/10 and notes it is not constant, but worsens with head movement. Ibuprofen provided mild relief. He reports occasional headaches related to the neck pain. He has a history of playing football years ago but denies any prior neck injuries. He did not seek emergency room care after the accident due to cost concerns.\nFindings\nPhysical examination reveals tenderness to palpation of the cervical muscles, positive findings on range of motion testing including pain with flexion, extension, and rotation. No swelling or bruising is noted on physical examination. Neurological examination reveals intact sensation and motor function.\nAssessment\nThe patient's symptoms and examination findings are consistent with a cervical strain secondary to whiplash.\nPlan",
